# Index Creation, Background

Which things are true about creating an index in the background in MongoDB. Check all that apply.


A mongod instance can only build one background index at a time per database.

(OK) Although the database server will continue to take requests, a background index creation still blocks the mongo shell that you are using to create the index.

(OK) Creating an index in the background takes longer than creating it in the foreground

In Mongo 2.2 and above, indexes are created in the background by default.


